    </table>
</div>
</p>
<p>It's easy: it works exactly the same as in the controller.</p>
<p>So, how do we get the user object? To find out - open up the homepage template. If
the User is logged in, let's welcome them by email.</p>
<p>Open the print tag and say <code>app.user ? app.user.email : 'Aquanauts'</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="9a97d4628f">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
            
            9 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="app/Resources/views/main/homepage.html.twig">app/Resources/views/main/homepage.html.twig</span>
        </div>
    </div>
    <table class="hljs code-block-table">
        <tbody class="js-tr-container">
                <tr>
